The paper proposes a framework to evaluate the robustness and generalization capability of deep learning models with respect to distribution shift. The experiments are conducted on image classification using CNN architectures, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, since the focus is on deep learning models and image classification, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories.
